summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 31582, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging, for public square purposes, of a portion of Block Two (2) of Davis Addition to The City of Seattle, and providing that the entire cost of said improvement shall be paid by special assessment upon the property specially benefited, in the manner provided by law", approved July 22, 1913 directing the Corporation Counsel to dismiss Cause No. 100734 in the Superior Court instituted upon said ordinance, and providing for the payment of costs, and declaring an emergency.
